 {[#]} {How to continue here?} 8... exd4 9. cxd4 Nxe4 $1 {We win the central
pawn opening up the 'e' file. White has to treat this as a sacrifice and make
use of his bishop pair. The position is still dynamically balanced.} 10. Ne2 (
10. Bxe4 Re8 $17) 10... d5 {We will try to keep our knight in the center until
he makes some concession to force us back.} 11. O-O Re8 12. Ng3 (12. Qc2 Bf5
13. cxd5 Qxd5 14. Nf4 Qc6 $11) 12... Nd7 {We want to bolster our knight on e4.}
13. Qc2 Ndf6 14. c5 Nxg3 15. hxg3 Bd7 $11 {White has some compensation with
the bishop pair but not more.} *


