 {[#]} {How to continue here?} 11... Nxb2 $1 {The most enterprising option.
There is an important concept in attack called the elimination of the 'b/g'
pawn. This is usually the key to getting to the opponent's king as it exposes
a lot of squares.} (11... a6 {is also good}) 12. Qxb2 Rb8 {The following
sequence is practically forced.} 13. a3 Rxb5 14. Bxf6 gxf6 15. axb4 Rxb4 (15...
Rxb4 16. Qa1 {A pretty nice square for the queen :) There is an alarming lack
of pawns in White's queenside.} exd5 17. e3 d4 18. exd4 c4 $1 19. d5 Qb6 $40 {
White has to continue playing only moves to survive here.}) *


