 {[#]} {How to continue here?} 13... Rd8 $1 {An important move to prepare e5
and open up the diagonal for the bishop.} (13... Nxc3 {is too early.} 14. Rxc3
e5 15. Nxe5 Nxe5 16. Re3 $1) 14. O-O e5 15. Nxe5 Nxe5 16. dxe5 Nxc3 17. Rxc3 d4
{The position has simplified and we reach an equal middlegame/endgame. I think
there are likely to be a few simplifications which result in a drawn rook
endgame.} 18. Rc1 Qxe5 19. Bd3 (19. Bf3 d3 $1 20. Qd2 Rb8 {The bishop will
come to f5 next and the pawn becomes a big asset for us.}) 19... Bf5 {This
happened in the game 1/2-1/2 (47) Wojtaszek,R (2733) -Kramnik,V (2792)
Dortmund 2018 and I think it is a good place for us to stop. The endgame is
pretty even.} *

