{[#] How to continue here?} 15... Bd7 $1 {Development
is the priority here.} 16. Qxb7 Nc6 17. Bd3 (17. Bc4 Qa4 18. O-O Ra7 19. Qb6
Nxg3 20. hxg3 Qb4 $11 {We get the queens off the board.}) 17... Nxg3 18. hxg3
Rab8 (18... Rab8 $1 {We exploit the drawback of the bishop on d3. The
following line is forced.} 19. Qxd7 Ne5 20. Bb1 Qxb1 21. Rxb1 Nxd7 22. Rxh6 (
22. Ke2 Kg7 23. b3 Rfc8 $11 {1/2-1/2 (36) Schleef, H-Faber, H freechess.de 2021
}) 22... Nc5 $44 {We easily have enough compensation for the pawn and the
endgame is pretty fighting.}) *

