 {[#]} {How to continue here?} 10... Kd7 $1 {This is a perfect position to
showcase our idea of bringing the king to the queenside. We want to then start
our play on the kingside with h5.} (10... e4 11. f4 $1 Nbd7 12. Nh3 $11) 11. e4
(11. Bd3 Kc7 12. Ne2 Qe7 13. a4 a5 14. Rb1 Rg8 $15 {h5 is coming up next.})
11... Kc7 12. Ne2 Nh5 {Now we will go for the move f5 next. It is a dream
version of KID for us as we have managed to rid of our worst piece and get a
super safe square for our king.} 13. Bf2 Qf8 $15 {[%cal Gf7f5]} *

